# VibeStream Pre-Launch: Session Walkthrough

## What Was Built

### Phase 1 — Bug Fixes (3 real bugs killed)
- **[VideoCard.tsx](file:///C:/GOLive/components/VideoCard.tsx)**: Fixed duplicate [formatViews](file:///C:/GOLive/app/studio/dashboard/page.tsx#18-24) branch and made the verified `✓` badge conditional on `is_verified` flag
- **[Sidebar.tsx](file:///C:/GOLive/components/Sidebar.tsx)**: Removed `Ninja`, `Valkyrae`, `MrBeast Gaming` fake users and `MrBeast Gaming` fake video thumbnails — replaced with live Supabase queries for real subscriptions and recent videos. Added **Shorts** nav link.
- **[Navbar.tsx](file:///C:/GOLive/components/Navbar.tsx)**: Avatar button now routes to `/studio/dashboard` instead of `/studio`.

---

### Phase 2 — Creator Dashboard (`/studio/dashboard`)
Full creator control center with:
- **Stats bar**: Total Views, Subscribers, Video count (live from Supabase)
- **Video Manager**: Edit title/visibility (Public/Unlisted/Private), Delete with confirmation
- **AI Studio CTA card**: Prominent entry point to the clip generator
- Feedback toasts (no more `alert()` boxes)

---

### Phase 3 — AI Studio (`/studio/ai-studio`) — $0/month
Apple-style step-by-step wizard:
1. Select a video from your library
2. **Gemini 2.5 Flash** (free tier, 250 req/day) returns 2–4 timestamped viral moments with scores
3. Creator picks a moment, clicks "Clip & Post as Short"
4. **ffmpeg** (open source) trims + converts to **9:16 reel format** (1080×1920) with blurred background fill for horizontal source videos
5. Clip uploaded to R2 + saved to DB as `is_short=true`, goes live on `/shorts`

**Cost: $0/month** — free Gemini API + open-source ffmpeg + existing R2 storage

> [!IMPORTANT]
> Add `GEMINI_API_KEY` to Vercel Environment Variables. Get it free at [aistudio.google.com](https://aistudio.google.com).

---

### Phase 4 — Shorts / Reels (`/shorts`)
- Full-screen vertical snap-scroll feed
- **Touch swipe** on mobile, **Arrow key** navigation on desktop
- Auto-play/pause on scroll, mute toggle
- Right-side action buttons: Like, Comment, Share, Follow
- Scroll position indicator dots
- Only shows videos where `is_short = true`

**SQL Migration**: [setup-shorts.sql](file:///C:/GOLive/setup-shorts.sql) — adds `is_short` column + index ✅ (run manually by user)

---

### Phase 5 — Profile / Channel Overhaul
- **Removed all external mock images**: no more `picsum.photos`, no more hardcoded Unsplash thumbnails
- **Dynamic gradient banners**: computed from username hash — no external dependencies
- **Separate Videos + Shorts tabs**: Shorts use a portrait 9/16 grid; Videos use the standard horizontal grid
- **About tab**: Shows real stats (subscribers, video count, member since year, bio)
- **In-channel search**: Filter videos by title within a creator's channel
- **Smart empty states**: Guide owners to upload or use AI Studio
- **Owner buttons**: "Dashboard" (→ `/studio/dashboard`) + "Customize" (→ `/studio`)

---

### Phase 6 — PWA / Mobile
- [public/manifest.json](file:///C:/GOLive/public/manifest.json) added — "Add to Home Screen" works on iOS + Android
- [app/layout.tsx](file:///C:/GOLive/app/layout.tsx) updated with manifest link + VibeStream branding in meta tags

---

### Studio Settings (`/studio`)
- Removed `picsum.photos` external mock banner — replaced with CSS gradient
- `alert()` → inline toast notifications
- "Creator Dashboard" back-link at top of page

